align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ticked Off Shammy</span><hr size=1> I would like to take a moment to voice my displeasure with the apparent lack of decorum and respect during our last guild meeting. In a nut shell we simply had &quot;way&quot; too much goofing off, emotes - casts - say/ooc/guild tells - etc., going on during what should be the &quot;serious&quot; portion of our meeting. <br>
<br>
I realize we're all here for fun, but there are times .. and our meeting being one .. that we need to simply chill a bit and take ourselves more seriously. Galadrid, our Officer Corps, and others are putting a lot of time and effort into _&quot;our&quot;_ guild and I think the best way to thank them is to be attentive when they are bringing the results of those efforts to the table. All they're asking for is 20-30 minutes every four to six weeks to convey the agenda they've prepared and the rest of the time we can do whatever we want, (um .. within reason).<br>
<br>
The &quot;administrative&quot; portion of our meeting would go smoother and quicker if we could all just find a comfortable spot to sit, and listen to what they need to say. Respond when required, in an appropriate manner &amp; save the horseplay for when the agenda has been covered.<br>
<br>
We've had very orderly meetings in the past and I'm sure that with a little self restraint, patience and awareness we can do so from here on out. It's just a matter of showing them, each other and ourselves a bit of respect and common courtesy.<br>
<br>
That too much to ask?<br>
<br>
T'Dan<br>
<br>
